Today I was very low on energy.
Although doing yoga every day, I didn't do what I needed to do.
Through this journey I've learned that my regular yoga practice is just a part of taking care of myself.
It  makes me feel good and helps me feel better when I'm down.

However, it doesn't magically solve my problems. 
Positive self talk and the way I treat others are essentials too.
In addition, the mantra "the breath always comes first" is a golden rule.

Still,  I forget things.
I forget to take mantras off the yoga mat and I feel that something doesn't feel right.
Yet, it takes me some time to realise what exactly.
A lot of times I forget to breath.
I don't know why but my breath becomes very shallow.
That's when my brain believes that something isn't right and tension builds.

Still, I've learned those mantras and what's been learned once can be remembered. 
"What's been asleep can be waken up."

Sometimes I forget that self care is an everyday act.
But today I was brave and took care of myself.
I surrendered and let go after holding on for too long...

...and it felt amazing.
Another very challenging practice but I pushed through and feel I am getting stronger.  So looking forward to day 30 yeah!   Namaste!

Today, practice felt absolutely great. I noticed some frustration and irritation I had towards myself and realized how I truly subconsciously project this onto my family and onto myself.
Lying in Savasana, realizing tomorrow will be the last day..it has come so soon!
I envisioned myself as who I was when I first started this journey 33 days ago (33 days because three days halfway in I was bed ridden with a cold)  but I remember the reason I started this whole journey.
Day 1 you asked us to ask ourselves why we‚Äôre here. Immediately I knew why I was showing up..
Self love.
Self confidence.
Strength in all aspects.
These past few years..when I honestly first started to practice yoga with you..have been so dark for me..so much releasing being done and so much light entering my heart.
I recently got out of a really beautiful and loving relationship..but there were somethings within our own selves that are desperately in the process of healing, which wouldn‚Äôt have been evident without the relationship.
But I was dependent on my happiness in this relationship..I was hurting so bad.
I remember the first couple of weeks in this yoga journey, i would show up on the mat and off the mat throughout my day..dark emotions and feelings came to the surface and during that time..I was SO scared it was never going to end. I was so scared that I wouldn‚Äôt overcome this tragic pain.
But here I am..day 29 and I feel refreshed. The deep pain I felt then has faded away and I didn‚Äôt even realize it until i stopped and realized all the beautiful work I have so far done for myself and will continue to create. I feel happy and in love with myself and my life and everything that makes up this entire YOUniverse.
Some days, of course I still feel sad..some days I am washed over with melancholy.
But when I allow rather than try to explain or make up a reason as to why I‚Äôm feeling natural human emotion.. I suffer LESS.
I‚Äôve become less controlling over my life and more allowing to let Source unfold my abundance right in front of me.
Thank you Adriene..I am so thankful for your role that you play in this world. You have always been such a great friend and I appreciate you. I wish I could hug you personally and tell you how much I love you!
